<div id="review_3282110892" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3282110892" />
    <a title="Faith Justice" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4243191-faith-justice"><img alt="Faith Justice" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442509839p2/4243191.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3282110892?book_show_action=true">Apr 19, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Faith Justice" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Faith Justice" href="/user/show/4243191-faith-justice">Faith Justice</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="ebook 9781784080686" href="/book/show/21347194-the-summer-of-the-danes">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3282110892" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2149633163415159334">I&apos;ve never read a bad Cadfael story, but (for me) they do range from the &quot;meh&quot; to &quot;better than average&quot; with most falling in the 3-star &quot;liked it--enjoyable diversion&quot; category. This one was closer to &quot;OK.&quot; Peters strays away from focusing on Cadfael and gets involved in Welsh/Dane politics with a large cast of characters having conflicting and confusing agendas, complicated by tongue-twisting names. There is a murder early in the story, but the search for the murderer disappears in favor of sto</span>
  <span id="freeText2149633163415159334" style="display:none">I've never read a bad Cadfael story, but (for me) they do range from the "meh" to "better than average" with most falling in the 3-star "liked it--enjoyable diversion" category. This one was closer to "OK." Peters strays away from focusing on Cadfael and gets involved in Welsh/Dane politics with a large cast of characters having conflicting and confusing agendas, complicated by tongue-twisting names. There is a murder early in the story, but the search for the murderer disappears in favor of story lines about an impossible romance and a rebellious younger brother to a Welsh prince. Cadfael makes only token appearances and doesn't solve the murder. The other stories didn't grab me with any urgency.</span>
  <a data-text-id="2149633163415159334" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


