  <span id="freeText8817137757544351649" style="display:none">Love, love, love this particular installment in the series. It brings back a several favorite characters, introduces a couple of new favorites, and takes Cadfael the full width of his native Wales. What more could any fan want? There is admittedly less of the usual Cadfaelian murder mystery element in this tale and more political intrigue and strategy. However, that difference provides a fascinating glimpse into the social structures of both the Welsh and Dano-Irish cultures of this shifting period and place. Easily my personal overall favorite of the series so far, which is saying something because I have yet to be disappointed with any of them.</span>
